cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Charbonnier loss functions and recursive layers suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, respectively.
